00:15:38.010 --> 00:15:39.480
I'm not a huge fan of it.

00:15:39.480 --> 00:15:40.980
So I think it's much cleaner.

00:15:40.980 --> 00:15:42.800
And also the fact
that filtering

00:15:42.800 --> 00:15:43.680
tends to be an action.

00:15:43.680 --> 00:15:44.940
It's not really navigation.

00:15:44.940 --> 00:15:46.560
It's kind of acting upon
the data you've

00:15:46.560 --> 00:15:49.180
already navigated to.

00:15:49.180 --> 00:15:51.565
It definitely maps to an action,
and therefore, like

00:15:51.565 --> 00:15:54.773
the right-hand side of the
action in Androids models, so.

00:15:54.773 --> 00:15:55.720
I think this is much better.

00:15:55.720 --> 00:15:57.000
ROMAN NURIK: Exactly.

00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:59.760
You'll notice here that there's
kind of an Up button

00:15:59.760 --> 00:16:02.220
or a Back button inside of
the navigation drawer.

00:16:02.220 --> 00:16:05.250
Anytime you see that, definitely
try to avoid that.

00:16:05.250 --> 00:16:07.770
The only type of hierarchy you
should have within the drawer

00:16:07.770 --> 00:16:09.850
is collapsible sections.

00:16:09.850 --> 00:16:11.480
So you can have some kind
of a collapsible

00:16:11.480 --> 00:16:12.400
item within the drawer.

00:16:12.400 --> 00:16:15.960
But definitely if you have
different entire contexts

00:16:15.960 --> 00:16:17.786
within the drawer, that's
something that you

00:16:17.786 --> 00:16:20.430
should try to avoid.

00:16:20.430 --> 00:16:22.370
I think there may have
been-- no, that's it.

00:16:22.370 --> 00:16:28.620
So that was the entire type of
redesign we did for this app.

