00:24:35.140 --> 00:24:37.100
bar affordances.

00:24:37.100 --> 00:24:39.120
I'd love to see them get
slightly closer to a stock

00:24:39.120 --> 00:24:40.690
action bar presentation.

00:24:40.690 --> 00:24:43.420
But largely they're following
the spirit of, oh, I know

00:24:43.420 --> 00:24:44.640
where to look for navigation.

00:24:44.640 --> 00:24:47.510
Oh, I know where to look
for actions to perform.

00:24:47.510 --> 00:24:49.590
So here, these are good examples
of where they're

00:24:49.590 --> 00:24:51.330
doing something custom and
trying to bring their own

00:24:51.330 --> 00:24:52.460
personalities, but
marrying them

00:24:52.460 --> 00:24:53.735
with the Android patterns.

00:24:56.460 --> 00:24:58.525
ROMAN NURIK: So visual design?

00:24:58.525 --> 00:25:02.433
NICK BUTCHER: Yeah, so the last
way I wanted to look at

00:25:02.433 --> 00:25:03.990
it is looking at the
visual design.

00:25:03.990 --> 00:25:08.880
So this is really a mixture of
both your own look and feel

00:25:08.880 --> 00:25:11.290
along with the Android
look and feel.

00:25:11.290 --> 00:25:16.300
So the idea here is to blend
your brand, your own identity,

00:25:16.300 --> 00:25:17.670
with the Android
look and feel.

00:25:17.670 --> 00:25:20.440
So one example of this
might be things like

00:25:20.440 --> 00:25:22.610
